title: Grateful Dead Live at Community War Memorial Auditorium on 1982-04-09

reviews.review_text:
Another Gem This is a another under the radar shows, They are for sure firing on all cylinders. Listening to this one again this morning for maybe the 4th or 5th time in all these years. It's a well played show with few of my favorite song selections To Lay Me Down as one of them. 
 To me all songs are played very nicely . Check out the 4 minute mark of Chinacat , its one of those moments when we as heads would be dancing along grooving to song and bam they hit us with that little bit extra and we all look at each other around us dancing like fools and huge shit eating grins. Also love the way the pull of the end of the show with Going down the road Satisfaction. And as some said in one of the other reviews Brokedown is always a good encore.
